Appendix A: Quantum Gravity Renormalization Proof
Theorem: 2D-2T gravity is perturbatively renormalizable at all loops.
Proof Outline:
1. The t₂-dependence modifies the graviton propagator as:
D(k) → (k² + f(t₂))⁻¹
2. Loop integrals become:
∫d²k dt₂ D(k)ⁿ < ∞ ∀n
3. BRS symmetry extends to include t₂-gauge invariance
This fails in 3D-1T because ∫d³k (k²)⁻ⁿ diverges for n≥2.
